TITLE: Complete React App with LiveCodes Example
DESCRIPTION: A complete example of a React application using the LiveCodes component with initial HTML, CSS, and JavaScript content. This demo also opens the console by default for viewing output.
SOURCE: https://github.com/live-codes/livecodes/blob/develop/docs/docs/sdk/react.mdx#2025-04-13_snippet_7

LANGUAGE: jsx
CODE:
```
import LiveCodes from "livecodes/react";

const App = () => {
  const params = {
    html: "<h1>Hello World!</h1>",
    css: "h1 {color: blue;}",
    js: 'console.log("Hello, World!")',
    console: "open",
  };

  return <LiveCodes params={params} />;
};

export default App;

```

