TITLE: Defining and Using a User Class in Ruby WebAssembly
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates basic Ruby class definition with attribute accessors, constructor, and custom methods. It creates a User class with a name property and an admin check method, then instantiates it and outputs results to the console.
SOURCE: https://github.com/live-codes/livecodes/blob/develop/docs/docs/languages/ruby-wasm.mdx#2025-04-13_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: ruby
CODE:
```
class User
  attr_accessor :name

  def initialize(name)
    @name = name
  end

  def admin?
    @name == 'Admin'
  end
end

user = User.new('Bob')

# the output will go to the console
puts user
puts user.admin?

```

