TITLE: LiveCodes SDK as Svelte Action with Cleanup
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates a more robust implementation of the LiveCodes SDK as a Svelte action. It includes proper cleanup when the component is unmounted, ensuring better resource management.
SOURCE: https://github.com/live-codes/livecodes/blob/develop/docs/docs/sdk/svelte.mdx#2025-04-13_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: html
CODE:
```
<script>
  import { createPlayground } from 'livecodes';
  let options = {
    // embed options
  };

  const livecodes = (node, opts) => {
    let playground = $state(null);
    const ready = new Promise(async (res) => {
      playground = await createPlayground(node, opts);
      res();
    });
    return { destroy: () => ready.then(() => playground?.destroy()) };
  };
</script>

<div use:livecodes="{options}"></div>
```

