DESCRIPTION: The JavaScript output compiled from the TypeScript Greeter class. This shows how TypeScript code transpiles to JavaScript with constructor initialization of class properties.
SOURCE: https://github.com/live-codes/livecodes/blob/develop/docs/docs/features/intellisense.mdx#2025-04-13_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: js
CODE:
```
export class Greeter {
  constructor() {
    this.morningGreetings = ['Good morning', 'Have a good day', 'How are you today?'];
    this.eveningGreetings = ['Good evening', 'Good night', 'Sleep well'];
  }
  randomSelector(array) {
    return array[Math.floor(Math.random() * array.length)];
  }
  morning() {
    return this.randomSelector(this.morningGreetings);
  }
  evening() {
    return this.randomSelector(this.eveningGreetings);
  }
}
```

