TITLE: Event Handling for Custom Settings in LiveCodes
DESCRIPTION: This code implements event handlers for the custom settings inputs. It saves input values to localStorage when they change and provides a way to reset values to their defaults.
SOURCE: https://github.com/live-codes/livecodes/blob/develop/docs/docs/advanced/custom-settings.mdx#2025-04-13_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
// handle input changes
const handleApiKeyChange = () => {
  localStorage.setItem('custom-apiKey', apiKeyInput.value);
};
const handleServerChange = () => {
  localStorage.setItem('custom-server', serverInput.value);
};
const handleTimeoutChange = () => {
  localStorage.setItem('custom-timeout', timeoutInput.value);
};

// attach event listeners
apiKeyInput.addEventListener('change', handleApiKeyChange);
serverInput.addEventListener('change', handleServerChange);
timeoutInput.addEventListener('change', handleTimeoutChange);

// add a reset button
const resetButton = document.createElement('button');
resetButton.textContent = 'Reset';
resetButton.addEventListener('click', () => {
  localStorage.removeItem('custom-apiKey');
  localStorage.removeItem('custom-server');
  localStorage.removeItem('custom-timeout');
  apiKeyInput.value = '';
  serverInput.value = '';
  timeoutInput.value = '';
});
customSettings.querySelector('.panel-body')?.appendChild(resetButton);
```

